In this guidebook, the autor and publisher Federico Franzini arranged the text accoring to the recruiting format characterizing roman guidebooks at the time. The first section dedicated to the seven churches is followed by the description of other significant churches categorized by their location in Rome. The third section is the guida romana, a three day tour of Rome in which the author takes the visitor across time and space highlighting the most important sites. The final section is a description of the antiquities of Rome detailed according to its districts as known at the time. As in Pompilio Totti Ritratto di Roma moderna, the entry dedicated to Santa Martina repeats verbatim Panciroli’s text from 1625 mentions the Compagnia dei Pittori (founded 1478) and the demolition of the Church of San Luca near Santa Maria Maggiore by Sisto V during the urban renovation of Rome in 1588.
